for example we want date as per our norms like 

21st tuesday at 21:20:28

then use select DATE_FORMAT();

SELECT DATE_FORMAT(NOW(), '%D %a at %T');

if we want of the format 
that the result is 04/16/23

capital alphabet with the suffix indicates the day with 'st'

like above it is written that day is 21st

there are various other like %d/%m/%y
for day/month/year

for example table is given with jd,jt,jdt

and we have to apply this date format to the jdt 

then we will use it by 

select jdt,DATE_FORMAT(jdt,'%D %a at %k') from table_name;
in dateformat jdt is written to tell what to which column we have to apply the format

select DATEDIFF('2025-06-03','2025-06-08'); RESULT IS -5
select DATEDIFF('2025-06-08','2025-06-03'); RESULT IS 5 































